From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Handle missing RTS package in Stage0 package database

When cross-version bootstrapping (e.g., using GHC 9.6.7 to build GHC 9.2.8),
we deliberately skip registering RTS at Stage0 to avoid ABI incompatibility.
The bootstrap GHC's RTS has different symbols than our locally-built RTS,
and Stage0 utilities link against bootstrap libs expecting bootstrap's RTS.

However, the hackRtsPackage function in Cabal/Parse.hs expects exactly one
RTS package in the installed package database. When RTS is missing (because
we skipped registration), it errors with "No (or multiple) GHC rts package
is registered!".

This patch modifies hackRtsPackage to return the index unchanged when no
RTS package is found. The bootstrap GHC will fall back to its global package
database which has the compatible RTS.

--- a/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
@@ -232,14 +232,19 @@ resolveContextData context@Context {..} = do
         hackRtsPackage index | null (C.allPackages index) = index
         -- ^ do not hack the empty index
         hackRtsPackage index = case C.lookupPackageName index (C.mkPackageName "rts") of
+            -- Normal case: exactly one RTS package found, hack its options
             [(_, [rts])] -> C.insert rts {
                 Installed.ldOptions   = [],
                 Installed.libraryDirs = filter (not . ("gcc-lib" `isSuffixOf`))
                                                (Installed.libraryDirs rts)} index
-            -- GHC <= 6.12 had @$topdir/gcc-lib@ in their @library-dirs@ for the
-            -- 'rts' package, which causes problems when we try to use the
-            -- in-tree @mingw@, due to accidentally picking up the incompatible
-            -- libraries there. So we filter out @gcc-lib@ from the RTS's
-            -- @library-dirs@ here.
-            _ -> error "No (or multiple) GHC rts package is registered!"
+                -- GHC <= 6.12 had @$topdir/gcc-lib@ in their @library-dirs@ for the
+                -- 'rts' package, which causes problems when we try to use the
+                -- in-tree @mingw@, due to accidentally picking up the incompatible
+                -- libraries there. So we filter out @gcc-lib@ from the RTS's
+                -- @library-dirs@ here.
+            -- Cross-bootstrap case: RTS not in Stage0 DB (deliberately skipped).
+            -- Return index unchanged - bootstrap GHC uses its global DB's RTS.
+            [] -> index
+            -- Multiple RTS packages is still an error
+            _ -> error "Multiple GHC rts packages registered!"

         (buildInfo, modules, mainIs) = biModules (C.localPkgDescr lbi')
